# .github/CODEOWNERS
# 
# This file defines who is responsible for code in this repository.
# GitHub will automatically request reviews from these users/teams when
# files they "own" are modified in a pull request.
#
# Documentation: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# Syntax:
# pattern email|@username|@org/team-name
#
# Order matters! Later matches take precedence over earlier ones.

# =============================================================================
# DEFAULT OWNERS
# =============================================================================
# These owners will be the default owners for everything in the repo.
# Unless a later match takes precedence, they will be requested for review.

# * @yourusername

# =============================================================================
# EXAMPLE: SOLO DEVELOPER (Your Current Setup)
# =============================================================================
# For a solo developer, keep it simple:

# * @yourusername
# /.github/ @yourusername
# /deployment/ @yourusername

# =============================================================================
# EXAMPLE: SMALL TEAM (2-5 people)
# =============================================================================

# # Default owners for all files
# * @lead-dev @tech-lead
# 
# # Frontend code
# /src/components/ @frontend-dev @lead-dev
# /src/pages/ @frontend-dev
# /src/styles/ @frontend-dev @designer
# 
# # Backend/API integration
# /src/api/ @backend-dev @lead-dev
# /src/services/ @backend-dev
# 
# # Infrastructure and deployment
# /.github/ @devops-engineer @lead-dev
# /deployment/ @devops-engineer
# /.ebextensions/ @devops-engineer
# /Dockerfile @devops-engineer
# 
# # Documentation
# /docs/ @lead-dev @tech-writer
# *.md @lead-dev
# 
# # Configuration files
# package.json @lead-dev @frontend-dev
# tsconfig.json @lead-dev @frontend-dev
# vite.config.ts @lead-dev @frontend-dev

# =============================================================================
# EXAMPLE: LARGER TEAM (World-Class Company Style)
# Based on how companies like GitHub, Stripe, and Vercel structure theirs
# =============================================================================

# # ==================================================
# # Global Owners (Fallback)
# # ==================================================
# * @org/engineering-leads
